the Assembly for Leeds and Grenville, 1821, 1825, and again in 1832. A
strong supporter of the union of Upper and Lower Canada. Appointed a
puisne judge of the Court of Queen's Bench, 1837. =Bib.=: Read, _Lives
of the Judges_.

